results.title: More foreign students set to be eligible for Japan government scholarships
results.description: The Japanese government plans to expand the scope of foreign university students eligible for its scholarships from April to provide more academic opportunities to children of the country's growing number of foreign workers, according to officials. The education ministry is set to include in the target students who are residing in the country with their parents under a "dependent" visa on condition they have completed education through elementary, junior high and high school level in Japan and intend to work and stay in the country after graduating from university, they said. results.title: Royal insider reveals when the Princess of Wales plans to address speculation over her health
results.description: With speculation rife about Catherine, Princess of Wales' condition following her January abdominal surgery, the palace has already had to jump the gun and inform the public of the royal's condition.But now, a source close to the Wales family claims that all the public have to do is wait.The insider says Kate and Prince William will be more forthcoming about the diagnosis and recovery past Easter, when the Princess of Wales is due to start attending engagements again.﻿READ MORE: Diana faced 'more danger' than Kate, says the late Princess of Wales' brother Charles Spencer﻿The source told The Times "They are at their most open when out interacting with members of the public and I can see a world in which the princess might discuss her recovery out on engagements. If she was going to do it, that's how she would do it.The source, who is said to be a friend of Catherine's, says the couple "want to be clear and more open", but that "they're not going to be rushed." ﻿Another source told the publication that what is unfolding is exactly what they said would happen – the royal would have two weeks of recovery in hospital and then start working again after Easter.﻿READ MORE: How a single paparazzi photo broke up Kristen Stewart and Robert Pattinson﻿The couple may provide more insight into the royal's recovery with a photo released on ﻿April 23, marking Prince Loui's sixth birthday.An aide told the Sunday Times: ﻿"They appreciate the public's love and affection for their children and know there is a public appetite to see them on their birthdays."But there is no "firm decision" on whether Kate will be the one to take the picture, or if they will leave it to a professional.READ MORE: Queen Elizabeth 'really rocked' by Charles and Diana's troubled marriage, royal expert saysThe rumour mill has been churning for weeks, first beginning three weeks ago when the public created wild conspiracy theories and jokes about the royal's whereabouts.It caused Kensington Palace to release a statement, with a representative telling The Sun, "We were very clear from the outset that the Princess of Wales was out until after Easter and Kensington Palace would only be providing updates when something was significant."﻿Then came the paparazzi shot in the car and soon after the highly discussed photoshopped snap of the mum with her three children creating even more of a frenzy.﻿﻿For a daily dose of 9Honey, subscribe to our newsletter hereKate apologised for the gaffe via an Instagram story. In a post on the Prince and Princess of Wales' official social media accounts, Kate said that "like many amateur photographers, I do occasionally experiment with editing"."I wanted to express my apologies for any confusion the family photograph we shared yesterday caused," she signed off the message with her initial, C.
